Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Replace the Alert Center's 3s polling with push-based freshness via
the existing `GET /api/alerts/stream` SSE endpoint. Polling is kept
as a 30s safety net so the page still self-heals if the SSE channel
drops or the tab is backgrounded long enough to miss events.

## What changes

1. `artifacts/godsview-dashboard/src/hooks/useEventSource.ts`
   - New `AlertStreamEvent` type — mirrors backend fireAlert payload
     (`type`, `severity`, `message`, `details`, `timestamp`) and stays
     loose (`[key: string]: unknown`) to accommodate Phase 5 scheduler
     events that pass through the same pipeline.
   - New `useAlertStream(enabled)` specialized hook — thin wrapper
     around `useEventSource<AlertStreamEvent>` with `events: ["alert"]`.
     Inherits the parent hook's exponential-backoff auto-reconnect,
     `Last-Event-ID` replay, and 100-event client buffer.

2. `artifacts/godsview-dashboard/src/pages/alert-center.tsx`
   - Top-level page component now calls `useAlertStream(true)` and
     `useQueryClient()`; on every event (detected via `eventCount`
     delta in a `useEffect`) it invalidates the six Alert Center
     React Query caches so they refetch against the Phase 8
     endpoints immediately.
   - New `<LiveConnectionBadge>` in the page header renders one of
     "Live / Connecting… / Offline / Reconnecting" with the running
     event count — gives operators a glance-level signal of whether
     the page is receiving push.
   - Active feed polling backed off from 3s → 30s (push is primary).

3. `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md`
   - New "Alert Center Live Push (Phase 9)" subsection under the
     Phase 6 SLO section documenting the end-to-end push path.

